Approval of Domestic Modification and Repair Designs 
1.0 INTRODUCT ION 
1.1 Purpose 
The purpose of this Staff Instru ction (SI) is to  provide general information and basic procedures 
relating to: 
(a) The review and approval of Canadian design changes to the typ e design of aeronautical 
products as governed by Chapter 513 of the Airworthiness Manual (AWM); 
(b) The original issue of certificates and follow-on revisions to: 
(i) Supplemental Type Certificates (STC); 
(ii) Limited Supplemental Type Certificates (LSTC); and 
(iii) Repair Design Certificates (RDC); 
(c) The evaluation of applications  by Transport Canada Civil Aviation (TCCA) and 
submission to foreign civil aviation auth orities, on behalf of Cana dian applicants, for the 
issue of corresponding foreign approvals.  
1.2 Guidance Applicability 
This document is applicable to T ransport Canada Civil Aviatio n (T CCA) Headquarters and 
Regional personnel including delegates.  
1.3 Des cription of Changes 
This SI can cels and repla ces Aircraft Certification Staff Instruction (ACS I) 22 , Issu e 02, d ated 
2000-08-09.   The revision was used as an opportunity to ca ncel other guidance material and  
include the content into this document.  The Changed Product Rule (CPR) has been incorporated 
into this document, as have Instructions for Continued Airworthiness.  Further, certificate samples 
have been added to the appendix in order to aid in the national consistency of certificate format.  
Sample cover letters a re added to support applications to the FAA by Cana dian applicants. The 
overall fo rmat of the do cument h as b een changed to refle ct th e work that i s b eing done in  
mapping the certificate approval process. 
