3.0 BACKG ROUND 
Consistent with the provisi ons outlined in Chapter 513 of the AWM, a major chang e to the typ e 
design of a n aeronautical product, through a modification or a repair, requires approval by the 
Minister. 
4.0 EXEMPT FLIGHT AUTHORITIES 
(1) The procedures in this SI are not applicable to domestic changes in the following cases:  
(a) Aircraft that will be operating under the following flight authorities: 
(i) Special Certificate of Airworthiness – Amateur Built; 
(ii) Special Certi ficate of Ai rworthiness –  Limited (reference Main tenance and 
Manufacturing Staff Instruction (MSI) 52; 
(iii) Special Certificate of Airworthiness – Owner Maintenance; and  
(iv) Flight Permit – Specific Purpose; 
(b) Design changes approved under Chapter 511 of the AWM. 
5.0 PROJECT MANAGEMENT AND COORDINATION 
5.1 Project Application 
(1) The applicant must submit an application for the issuance of a Canadian approval in accordance 
with the requirements set forth in Chapter 513 of the AWM. 
(2) The application is made to the RMAC using Transport Canada Form 26-0469 and is to be signed 
by the applicant.  An alternate process consistent with section 513.04 of the AWM may be used if 
the process has been approved by TCCA, such as NAPA-NDWL. 
(3) The following items, at a minimum, should be submitted with the application to initiate a project: 
(a) Changed Product Rule (CPR) decision record; 
