APPENDIX B – PROJECTS REQUIRING HQ NOTIFICATION 
The following items should be considered when determining the need to involve headquarters upfront in a 
certification program. 
(1) Ne w technologies; 
(2) Software development or changes to software in flight-critical systems; 
(3) “Novel or unusual” design features; 
(4) Substantial changes in gross weight; 
(5) Substantial changes to the propulsion system; 
(6) Substantial changes in landing gear arrangement; 
(7) Revisions to, or establishment of, new AWL; 
(8) A proposed alternative means of compliance with an Airworthiness Directive; 
(9) Findings of equivalent safety or exemptions; 
(10) Substantial technical assistance from HQ specialists; or 
(11) Any other project likely to be controversial in nature. 

